##Five diaries: People no longer trust each other, changed three sets of clothes a day

Wechat, FINANCEAPP

Features, tencent news tencent financial official account, here to read finance!

For the city, although I was prepared, but did not expect to come so soon.

He Pinhui, editor, Liu Peng, is a contributing writer to periscope, a tencent news article

I am a native of Wuhan, where I live less than three kilometers from the source of the outbreak, the south China Seafood Market, and have been in Wuhan since the outbreak was first discovered. During this time, I've gone from not caring, to gradually panicking, to many near collapse.

On January 23, the situation reached its most serious stage: Wuhan announced that it would close all flights, trains, buses, subways and so on. Now, five days after I was shut down, my self doubt and mood gradually calmed down in my self isolation. The only uncertainty was whether my household supplies would be guaranteed if I ran out, but I could only do my bit, keeping a few notes, and staying in the House, is the best thing a normal person can do.

##Nobody cared at first

Back in the early days of the storm, on December 12,2019, the first patient was discovered, but to me it was just a piece of social news that was passed by.

On December 31,2019, a red-headed document with information about the illness in Wuhan went viral on Facebook, but the authorities did not say anything at the time and vigorously refuted rumors. The next day, eight netizens who posted and reposted false news about pneumonia were investigated and prosecuted, and once again, the news was treated as an after dinner conversation piece.

Later, in a series of briefings, I slowly pay attention to this matter, but thought, action did not pay attention. I, a Wuhan citizen, still take the crowded subway, in a training institution to prepare for the city test. But during this period, due to chance encounter, or say is real in Wuhan, some "minor details" of the situation, affect my understanding of the whole event.

On January 14, my father was drunk, but my mother and I dragged my father to the nearest hospital, the Central Hospital of Wuhan (Houhu Hospital area) , which was also the first hospital to be diagnosed with pneumonia.

I knew all about this hospital before, but we were able to get in because it was so close to home. It still shocks me to think about it: The hospital's emergency room was a madhouse near 12 a.m. , and the staff were not fully armed, but I was slightly alarmed by the unusually large number of people. One doctor told me that more than 40"suspected flu" patients were admitted that day.

But on the go, none of them wore masks. My mom snapped up an empty bed so my dad could lie down. I am full of inexplicable alert to these comings and goings, although do not know what the disease, but in which I feel half a foot into the gates of hell. So I asked the doctor for three masks at the last minute, and as soon as my dad hung up, I ran home. It was also the first contact with a potential outbreak, but the feeling of fear when I returned home was completely left in the hospital without much thought.

After the hospital the next night, received a call from a friend from other places, told me that Jiangsu Province has started a Preplan, let me pay attention to safety. I suddenly wake up, feel the seriousness of the situation, quickly bought a mask, alcohol cotton and other things. Medical supplies were plentiful, and prices were reasonable.

At that time, I told my parents must wear a mask, they laughed it off, I gave them the mask in the bag as a "talisman. ". Then I hastened to send them to both sides, only to receive a merciless sneer -- "it's not in the news, it's not that bad; we're in good health, we don't need masks. " As if the whole world was in no hurry, i'm the only one who's worried.

As a journalism student, I was really angry, but I was anxious to wait for the official media to report it so that the older generation would realize the seriousness of the problem.

On the night of January 20th, Academician Zhong Nanshan gave an interview to CCTV, which reported 218 cases of infection. Wuhan burst into flames. I stayed up that night to watch the SARS documentary, put together a timeline of the outbreak of SARS -- as if I hadn't been able to fall asleep since I discovered in November that the virus had disappeared in February, March, and May. The next day my parents went out wearing masks, and I was on the road trying to figure out if everyone was wearing the right one (N95 / KN95, surgical masks are best for prevention) . I breathed a sigh of relief and, feeling that everyone was aware of the seriousness of the problem, continued to walk on the crowded subway to the training facility, through the crowds, and continue my course.

In retrospect, many of the staff in the training institute had fever and cough and cold symptoms, but still insisted on going to work. Even one of the students who had a fever and asked for leave returned to the classroom with a cough. There was no smell of disinfectant in the air, and everything was as usual. After the outbreak, I discussed with my teachers whether I could suspend classes, which was considered unreasonable and hasty. But when another student asked for leave, I panicked and quickly packed my things and ran out of the classroom. The second I looked back at the building, I felt like I was running away.

##Drugstore Fright

I decided not to go to class training, also decided not to go out, but also want to buy some things at home stock, had no choice but to go to the supermarket. Eating breakfast in front of the supermarket, watching a person was 120 from the community to carry out alive, I was scared to death, quickly pulled my mother to leave. Although do not know whether it is pneumonia, but too many friends of the rumors really in front of the time, the heart is always trembling.

Shopping for groceries at a member's market in Qiaokou District. Perhaps because of the high level of consumption, most people have the right face masks, but I find that their employees still wear thin, substandard masks. When we went out for lunch at noon, at my prompting, the waiter put on a mask to ensure "superficial" psychological comfort.

Almost home, think of these days have shortness of breath symptoms, do not know is scared or how to go home across the pharmacy to buy drugs. The pharmacy was full of old people buying medicine. I lowered my head and hurried to the counter to ask the purchasing doctor where Oseltamivir was. She was not wearing a mask. She coughed and helped me get the medicine, at that time, the same cough was heard from other old people who were buying medicine. At that time, I felt that the sky was falling. My mind was blank and I dared not raise my head, as if the lower my head was, the more distance I could pull away from them, he paid the money carelessly and ran out of the pharmacy.

This is the third and final escape. When I got home, I was devastated. I cried with my dad in my arms, told them I wasn't going out, and told them to cancel all their New Year's dinners.

My home is too close to the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, belongs to the worst-hit areas, this more than 1,000 cases of potential sick people, there will be how much probability in my area of life?

I was proud of Wuhan when I was a child, but at this moment I wanted to escape from Wuhan. I had a hazy but clear view of what was to come. Now a lot of things can not be normalized solution, everything is in a state of emergency. Sealing off sections of some infectious source may be the best solution.

##Lack of trust

It wasn't supposed to be enforced until after the Spring Festival. Quickly and disorderly open a mobile phone to buy, from TMALL supermarket to Meituan take-out, one after another order, by the merchants back to find the shop order. When a 50-yuan picture of a cabbage appears on my friends' circle, it's hard for me to believe in the so-called "support" . Clearly yesterday like a refuge to buy half of the things, but always not enough, back and forth to count, see what is bad.

Early in the morning (early breakfast in Wuhan) , I explained the situation to my father and mother very seriously. I asked my father to take a plate of the family's food, distribute it according to the nutrition every day, and let my mother do a good job of household hygiene every day, sterilize it with 84 sooner or later. My parents still looked at me with half a smile and nodded frowzily.

When I suggested making a list of things to do every day with a small blackboard, my father couldn't help laughing and my mother gave him a pat on the back to give me some dignity on the surface. I was so angry, I broke my chopsticks and left! Shut the door of that moment, Sigh: Alas, obviously is oneself play child's temper.

Tidy up the mood, open the phone one after another to grandparents grandparents grandparents call friends told them not to go out. In the middle of the take-out call, I quickly let my father put on go out clothes, take a mask downstairs to get the package. Looking at my father's back as he went downstairs to get something, I not only thought of Zhu Ziqing's words, "that's when I saw his back, and my tears came down quickly. " . A moment ago I was angry with him, but my father is the pillar of the family, for our family out of all the wind and rain.

Dad Soon came up, I put together with him outside the door of the things, one by one to wipe the house, he quickly went downstairs to throw the bags outside the garbage can, back and forth several times. Dad walked through the door, and I let him change his clothes and put them on the balcony to blow.

Finally toss over, and hear the knock knock knock, I quickly prone on the door to see cat's eye, is a non-wearing mask of the Old Lady! I Stuck in the Middlen't want to open the door. The knock on the door became more and more urgent. My mother quickly told me to open the door. My father got up, passed me and was ready to open the door. I quickly got a mask for him, is this really the time for this? I immediately pulled my father in, prevaricate mother-in-law will close the door, Hook my father, ran to the toilet quickly with salt water gargle.

Then, I received a phone call from my college classmate. For the first time in my life, I did a simple telephone interview. I tried to tell her what I knew and saw in detail. Then I heard a knock on the door again. When I opened the door, I saw my father and mother-in-law standing at the door arguing without masks. I ran out and dragged my father to the door. My father pushed me in, he said to me, "we have to talk about this. GO INSIDE! " And he closed the door behind him. I broke down, shouting to my mother to persuade my father, and quickly took a mask, let him wear. I dragged my dad into the door with all my might, and watched the grey-haired grandmother's Surprised Eyes Fade into the crack of the door.

There was no trust anymore, and I needed to protect everyone in my family, so I asked my dad to change into his third outfit for the day.

##Self doubt

It was 1:00 in the afternoon, so I had a simple lunch and watched the roast with Amway's parents to make them happy. The morning was too much. I thought about it for a long time after dinner, and it felt like it was time to do something. I don't know if I'm infected in this time of crisis, so I might as well do something to help while I'm still healthy. So I immediately thought of graduate one when I studied with the psychology teacher, there are some data in the group, thinking of the need to drop everything, do something useful.

After I got in touch with my psychology major, I started researching, and as I was getting ready to read, my mom asked me to take a nap. Think of last night until two o'clock sleep, casual first rest. When I tried to get my dad to sleep, I saw him curled up on the couch, frowning at his cell phone. I asked him what he was watching, and he quickly turned off the news and said, nothing. I thought to myself, did I scare him too much in the morning, let him do something else. Read a novel.

But lay down the bed, toss and turn no sleep, over and over again to force themselves to sleep, no results. I had to get up. I felt so hot and weak. It's a rush. I need to eat something to get my strength back. As he nibbled on an apple, he listened to a recording of the outbreak: "The disease has no symptoms. Fever is not the only criterion. " "The truth should be known to the public. ".

Quickly took out the bedside thermometer, while measuring with my mother said, "I seem to have symptoms now! " Did Not Answer. I gawked at the glowing computer, wondering how it could be as fast as it could be. Five minutes up, I took a thermometer, my mother quickly asked "how many degrees? " , I said, "well, 36.5 less. " The heart of the stone fell.

##Mind repair

Since the accident, my mother has been very optimistic, but when CCTV New Year's Gala saw the Wuhan Reading Program, she could not help but shed tears, I came forward to hold. It chills me to see my parents watching CCTV New Year's Gala while she scours the news. On one side is the atmosphere of the New Year, on the other side is the difficult and difficult situation that ordinary people can not imagine, it is hard to let go.

After the Spring Festival gala, it was as if there had been a chaotic battle. As the gala drew to a close, people who had not yet fallen asleep began to actively forward rescue messages on their friends'circles and microblogs. Late at night, emotions like a flood of animals general outbreak, reached the pole. Disorder, powerlessness.

But at the start of the day, the mood heals. On the fourth day of the closing of the city, the first day of the Lunar New Year, my reaction was ahead of most people. I began to recover gradually from the ups and downs of my mood, and was able to lead a normal life, reduce my intake of news, study, listen to music, and do some proper exercise.

Life gradually began to get on track, I got up in the morning and finished the first handbook of epidemic prevention psychology in the afternoon. I sent it to the micro blog and the public account, thinking that I could calm everyone's mood from the psychological level within the limited scope.

Although I do not know how many people will see, for their psychological comfort and guidance, to do these things in the end is meaningful. But "done is better than not done" , with such a mentality, stick to it.

There are also friends looking for me, "need to chat" , "free can find me" . Greetings like this are very warm and touching. From a lack of trust, to letting go of your guard, your hearts become softer, and you bond with each other for warmth and comfort.

From now on, I began to appeal to everyone: At home all the less brush mobile phone, find friends and family chat, can not meet to do online friends, open video chat, away from the moment not worry. After all, man is a social animal, and nothing can happen to a man if he thinks for a moment.

But my parents are still on facebook. I don't know if it's real or not, but it's over. This year does not receive gifts, to receive short messages, we all cloud New Year, no disease no disaster no trouble. Watching them cooped up on the couch every day. Exercise of the matter put on the agenda, dragged them hard to dance the "small Apple" , two 40-50-year-old people in the home of the sight of the claws, I secretly shot down for you.

Life seems more and more peaceful after the blockade. But the only thing that bothers me is the shortage. A lot of people have gone out to buy, fortunately, the home store a lot of goods, did not join the fray. But such a closed day do not know how long to go, do not know the food ran out of the home, the materials in the end there is no guarantee. There's a lot we don't know. For the time being, I can only do my best, do what I can, do not go out, is the greatest contribution.
